  "body": "Hi Team,\r\n\r\nI am using an application that moves Ether from a \"from\" address to a \"to\" address as specified in the parameter of the API call. The application is a NodeJS app connected to a remote node (my own geth node). The issue is that when I issue successive transactions from same \"from\" address, it does not take the pending transactions into account and shows the same nonce.\r\n\r\nSo I get the error known transaction found or replacement transaction underpriced.\r\n\r\nNote: This setup worked fine with a previous version of geth 1.8.x\r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: 1.8.9-stable\r\nOS & Version: Ubuntu 16.04\r\nCommit hash: None\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nFor an address say X, if a transaction from X to Y for a value Z with Nonce 2 is pending, eth_getTransactionCount(X, 'pending') should return 3\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nFor an address say X, if a transaction from X to Y for a value Z with Nonce 2 is pending, eth_getTransactionCount(X, 'pending') returns 2 until that tx is mined.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\nFor an address X, Console the output of eth_getTransactionCount(X, 'pending') and then do a transaction from that address X. Console the out of eth_getTransactionCount(X, 'pending') immediately after the transaction.\r\n\r\n#### Backtrace\r\n\r\nNo Backtrace.\r\n",
